English:
Shinjuku has sooo many people.
But not a good man anywhere, LBR.
Chinese:
新宿這裡的人很多對吧～
啊啊～哪裡有好男人呢～
Korean:
신주쿠엔 역시 사람이 많네~
아~아, 어딘가에 좋은 남자 없을까.
German:
In Shinjuku gibt es sooo viele Leute.
Aber weit und breit kein guter Kerl, seien wir
doch mal ehrlich.

Chinese: 什麼？　你有事情想問我？

English:
Capturing the heart of a fair maiden, or whatever.
Hearing that kind of crap just makes you think
whoa, back up... 100% turnoff, JSYK.
Chinese:
光是說出要抓住少女心那種話，
就讓人很不以為然耶。
那樣根本就不帥。
Korean:
"소녀의 마음을 잡는다"니
그런 말을 입 밖에 낸 시점에서 글렀다는 느낌.
전―혀 매력이 느껴지지 않아.
German:
Das Herz einer holden Maid erobern und so weiter.
Wenn man so was hört, denkt man sich gleich,
Junge, mach mal langsam ... Das geht gar nicht.

English:
What? What're you all worked up about?
Now you've got me curious.
Chinese:
咦～？　你不是有事想問我嗎？
很讓人在意耶～
Korean:
응~? 뭔가 묻고싶은게 있었던거 아냐?
신경쓰이네~
German:
Was? Was hibbelst du denn so rum?
Jetzt will ich’s auch wissen.

English:
The one thing that will catch a girl's heart...
Well, it's not "things" at all.
Chinese:
我覺得到頭來，
禮物並不是抓住少女心的必要物品耶～
Korean:
소녀의 마음을 잡기 위해 필요한건
결국 물건이 아니라는 느낌인걸~
German:
Eine Sache, mit der man Frauen für sich
gewinnt ... Nein, es geht gar nicht um Sachen.

English:
The ultimate present to win over girls...
Hearing that kind of crap just makes you think
whoa, back up... 100% turnoff, JSYK.
Chinese:
光是說出要抓住少女心、究極的禮物那種話，
就讓人很不以為然耶。
那樣根本就不帥。
Korean:
소녀의 마음을 잡는다, 던가 궁극의 선물이라던가…
그런 말을 입 밖에 낸 시점에서 글렀다는 느낌.
전―혀 매력이 느껴지지 않아.
German:
Das ultimative Geschenk für Frauen ...
Wenn man so was hört, denkt man sich sofort,
Junge, mach mal langsam ... Das geht gar nicht.
